{
  "doc_id": "27166",
  "text": "Using c-fos as an activity marker, enhanced neuronal activity has been observed after social play behavior in several medial PFC regions, ie, anterior cingulate, prelimbic cortex (PrL) and infralimbic cortex (IL), as well as in orbitofrontal cortex (OFC) regions [CITATION_1] Gordon et al, 2002; [CITATION_2] . In keeping with these findings, the structure of social play and its sensitivity to social cues was found to be altered after neonatal lesions of the PFC or OFC [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
